Task:
Standard input conisits of a single line of text.

All of the characters in the text are digits.

Write a python script named sum-digits.py which writes the sum 
of those digits to standard output.

Solution:

#!/usr/bin/env python3

s = input()
num = len(s) - 1
total = 0

i = 0
while i < len(s):
  total = total + int(s[num])
  num = num - 1
  i = i + 1

print(total)
